\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 ever mindful of his mercy,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 55}as he promised to our ancestors,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 to Abraham and his descendants for ever.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 56}Mary stayed with Elizabeth about three months, and then returned to her home.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 57}When Elizabeth\uc1\u8217*s time came, she gave birth to a son;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 58}and her neighbors and relatives, hearing of the great goodness of the Lord to her, came to share her joy.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 59}A week later they met to circumcise the child, and were about to call him Zechariah after his father,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 60}when his mother spoke up, \uc1\u8220*No, he is to be called John.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 61}\uc1\u8220*You have no relation of that name!\uc1\u8221* they exclaimed;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 62}and they made signs to the child\uc1\u8217*s father, to find out what he wished the child to be called.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 63}Asking for a writing tablet, he wrote the words \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*His name is John.\uc1\u8217* Everyone was surprised{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 64}and immediately Zechariah recovered his voice and the use of his tongue, and began to bless God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 65}All their neighbors were awe-struck at this, and throughout the hill-country of Judea the whole story was much talked about.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 66}All who heard it kept it in mind, asking one another \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*What can this child be destined to become?\uc1\u8221* For the Power of the Lord was with him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 67}Then his father Zechariah was filled with the Holy Spirit, and, speaking under inspiration, said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 68}\uc1\u8220*Blessed is the Lord, the God of Israel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 who has visited his people and wrought their deliverance,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 69}and has raised up for us the strength of our salvation
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 in the house of his servant David \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 70}as he promised by the lips of his holy prophets of old \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 71}salvation from our enemies and from the hands of all who hate us,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 72}showing mercy to our ancestors,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 and mindful of his sacred covenant.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 

\par}

{\pard
\par}

