\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 77}to give his people the knowledge of salvation
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 through the forgiveness of their sins,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 78}through the tender mercy of our God,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 whereby the dawn will break on us from heaven,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 79}to give light to those who live in darkness and the shadow of death,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 and guide our feet into the way of peace.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 80}The child grew and became strong in spirit, and he lived in the wilds until the time came for his appearance before Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}About that time an edict was issued by the Emperor Augustus that a census should be taken of the whole Empire.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}(This was the first census taken while Quirinius was Governor of Syria).{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And everyone went to his own town to be registered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Among others Joseph went up from the town of Nazareth in Galilee to Bethlehem, the town of David, in Judea \uc1\u8211* because he belonged to the family and house of David \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}to be registered with Mary, his engaged wife, who was about to become a mother.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}While they were there her time came,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}and she gave birth to her first child, a son. And because there was no room for them in the inn, she swathed him around and laid him in a manger.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}In that same countryside were shepherds out in the open fields, watching their flocks that night,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}when an angel of the Lord suddenly stood by them, and the glory of the Lord shone around them; and they were seized with fear.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8220*Have no fear,\uc1\u8221* the angel said. \uc1\u8220*For I bring you good news of a great joy in store for all the nation.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}This day there has been born to you, in the town of David, a Savior, who is Christ and Lord.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And this will be the sign for you. You will find the infant swathed, and lying in a manger.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then suddenly there appeared with the angel a multitude of the heavenly Host, praising God, and singing \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}\uc1\u8220*glory to God on high,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 and on earth peace among those in whom he finds pleasure.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Now, when the angels had left them and gone back to heaven, the shepherds said to one another, \uc1\u8220*Let us go at once to Bethlehem, and see this thing that has happened, of which the Lord has told us.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}So they went quickly, and found Mary and Joseph, and the infant lying in a manger;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}and, when they saw it, they told of all that had been said to them about this child.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}All who heard the shepherds were astonished at their story,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}while Mary treasured in her heart all that they said, and thought about it often.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}And the shepherds went back, giving glory and praise to God for all that they had heard and seen. It had all happened as they had been told.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Eight days after the birth of the child, when it was time to circumcise him, he received the name Jesus \uc1\u8211* the name given him by the angel before his conception.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}When the period of purification of mother and child, required by the Law of Moses, came to an end, his parents took the child up to Jerusalem to present him to the Lord,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}in compliance with the Law of the Lord that every firstborn male will be dedicated to the Lord,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}and also to offer the sacrifice required by the Law of the Lord \uc1\u8211* a pair of turtle-doves or two young pigeons.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}There was at that time in Jerusalem a man named Simeon, a righteous and devout man, who lived in constant expectation of  Israel\uc1\u8217*s consulation, and under the guidance of the Holy Spirit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}It had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit that he should not die until he had seen the Lord\uc1\u8217*s Christ.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Moved by the Spirit, Simeon came into the Temple Courts, and, when the parents brought in the child Jesus, to do for him what was customary under the Law,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Simeon himself took the child in his arms, and blessed God, and said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}\uc1\u8220*Now, Lord, you will let your servant go,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 according to your word, in peace,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}for my eyes have seen the salvation
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}which you have prepared in the sight of all nations \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
1{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}a light to bring light to the Gentiles,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
2 and to be the glory of your people Israel.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}While the child\uc1\u8217*s father and mother were wondering at what was said about him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}Simeon gave them his blessing, and said to Mary, the child\uc1\u8217*s mother, \uc1\u8220*This child is appointed to be the cause of the fall and rise of many in Israel, and to be a sign much spoken against \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Yes, the sword will pierce your own heart \uc1\u8211* and so the thoughts in many minds will be disclosed.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}There was also a prophet named Hannah, a daughter of Phanuel and of the tribe of Asher. She was far advanced in years, having lived with her husband for seven years after marriage,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}and then a widow, until she had reached the age of eighty-four. She never left the Temple Courts, but, fasting and praying, worshiped God night and day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}At that moment she came up, and began publicly to thank God and to speak about the child to all who were looking for the deliverance of Jerusalem.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}When the child\uc1\u8217*s parents had done everything required by the Law of the Lord, they returned to Galilee to their own town of Nazareth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}The child grew and became strong and wise, and the blessing of God was on him.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}Every year the child\uc1\u8217*s parents used to go to Jerusalem at the Passover Festival.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}When Jesus was twelve years old, they went according to custom to Jerusalem,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}and had finished their visit; but, when they started to return, the boy Jesus remained behind in Jerusalem, without their knowing it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}Thinking that he was with their fellow travelers, they went one day\uc1\u8217*s journey before searching for him among their relatives and acquaintances;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}and then, as they did not find him, they returned to Jerusalem, searching everywhere for him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}It was not until the third day that they found him in the Temple Courts, sitting among the teachers, now listening to them, now asking them questions.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}All who listened to him marveled at his intelligence and his answers.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}His parents were amazed when they saw him, and his mother said to him, \uc1\u8220*My child, why have you treated us like this? Your father and I have been searching for you in great distress.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}\uc1\u8220*What made you search for me?\uc1\u8221* he answered. \uc1\u8220*Didn\uc1\u8217*t you know that I must be in my Father\uc1\u8217*s house?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 50}His parents did not understand what he meant.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}However he went down with them to Nazareth, and submitted himself to their control; and his mother treasured all that was said in her heart.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}And Jesus grew in wisdom as he grew in years, and gained the blessing of God and people.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Preparation

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
