{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}All who were present spoke well of him, and were astonished at the beautiful words that fell from his lips. \uc1\u8220*Isn\uc1\u8217*t Joseph\uc1\u8217*s son?\uc1\u8221* they asked.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u8220*Doubtless,\uc1\u8221* said Jesus, \uc1\u8220*you will remind me of the saying \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Doctor, cure yourself;\uc1\u8217* and you will say \uc1\u8216*Do here in your own country all that we have heard that has been done at Capernaum.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}I tell you,\uc1\u8221* he continued, \uc1\u8220*that no prophet is acceptable in his own country.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}There were, doubtless, many widows in Israel in Elijah\uc1\u8217*s days, when the heavens were closed for three years and six months, and a severe famine prevailed throughout the country;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}and yet it was not to one of them that Elijah was sent, but to a widow at Zarephath in Sidonia.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}And there were many lepers in Israel in the time of the prophet Elisha, yet it was not one of them who was made clean, but Naaman the Syrian.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}All the people in the synagogue, as they listened to this, became enraged.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Starting up, they drove Jesus out of the town, and led him to the brow of the hill on which their town stood, intending to hurl him down.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}But he passed through the middle of the crowd and went on his way.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Then Jesus went down to Capernaum, a city in Galilee. On the Sabbath he taught the people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}They were amazed at his teaching, because his words were spoken with authority.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}In the synagogue there was a man with the spirit of a foul demon in him, who called out loudly,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}\uc1\u8220*Stop! What do you want with us, Jesus of Nazareth? Have you come to destroy us? I know who you are \uc1\u8211* the Holy One of God!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}But Jesus rebuked the demon. \uc1\u8220*Be silent! Come out from him,\uc1\u8221* he said. The demon flung the man down in the middle of the people, and then came out from him, without causing him further harm.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}And they were all lost in amazement, and kept saying to one another, \uc1\u8220*What words are these? For he gives his commands to the foul spirits with a marvelous authority, and they come out.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}And rumors about Jesus traveled through every place in the region.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}On leaving the synagogue, Jesus went into Simon\uc1\u8217*s house. Now Simon\uc1\u8217*s mother-in-law was suffering from a severe attack of fever, and they asked Jesus to cure her.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}Bending over her, he rebuked the fever; the fever left her, and she immediately got up and began to take care of them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}At sunset, all who had friends suffering from various diseases took them to Jesus; and he placed his hands on everyone of them and cured them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}And even demons came out from many people, screaming \uc1\u8216*You are the Son of God.\uc1\u8217* Jesus rebuked them, and would not allow them to speak, because they knew that he was the Christ.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}At daybreak, Jesus went out and walked to a lonely spot. But crowds of people began to look for him; and they came to where he was and tried to detain him and prevent his leaving them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}Jesus, however, said to them, \uc1\u8220*I must take the good news of the kingdom of God to the other towns too, for that was why I was sent.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}And he continued to make his proclamation in the synagogues of Judea.
\par}

