{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}A centurion in the Roman army had a slave whom he valued, and who was seriously ill \uc1\u8211* almost at the point of death.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And, hearing about Jesus, he sent some Jewish elders to him, with the request that he would come and save his slave\uc1\u8217*s life.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}When they found Jesus, they earnestly implored him to do so. \uc1\u8220*He deserves the favor from you,\uc1\u8221* they said,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8220*For he is devoted to our nation, and himself built our synagogue for us.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}So Jesus went with them. But, when he was no great distance from the house, the centurion sent some friends with the message \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Do not trouble yourself, Sir; for I am unworthy to receive you under my roof.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}That was why I did not even venture to come to you myself; but speak, and let my manservant be cured.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}For I myself am a man under the orders of others, with soldiers under me; and if I say to one of them \uc1\u8216*Go,\uc1\u8217* he goes, and to another \uc1\u8216*Come,\uc1\u8217* he comes, and to my slave \uc1\u8216*Do this,\uc1\u8217* he does it.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Jesus was surprised to hear these words from him; and, turning to the crowd which was following him, he said, \uc1\u8220*I tell you, nowhere in Israel have I met with such faith as this!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And, when the messengers returned to the house, they found the slave recovered.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Shortly after, Jesus went to a town called Nain, his disciples and a great crowd going with him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Just as he approached the gate of the town, there was a dead man being carried out for burial \uc1\u8211* an only son, and his mother was a widow. A large number of the people of the town were with her.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}When he saw her, the Master was moved with compassion for her, and he said to her, \uc1\u8220*Do not weep.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Then he went up and touched the bier, and the bearers stopped; and Jesus said, \uc1\u8220*Young man, I am speaking to you \uc1\u8211* Rise!\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}The dead man sat up and began to talk, and Jesus restored him to his mother.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Everyone was awe-struck and began praising God. \uc1\u8220*A great prophet has arisen among us,\uc1\u8221* they said. \uc1\u8220*God has visited his people.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And this story about Jesus spread all through Judea, and in the neighboring countries as well.
\par}

