{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}All these events were reported to John by his disciples.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}So he summoned two of them, and sent them to the Master to ask \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Are you \uc1\u8216*the coming one,\uc1\u8217* or are we to look for someone else?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}When these men found Jesus, they said, \uc1\u8220*John the Baptist has sent us to you to ask \uc1\u8211* Are you \uc1\u8216*the coming one,\uc1\u8217* or are we to look for somebody else?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}At that very time Jesus had cured many people of diseases, afflictions, and wicked spirits, and had given many blind people their sight.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}So his answer to the question was, \uc1\u8220*Go and report to John what you have witnessed and heard \uc1\u8211* the blind recover their sight, the lame walk, the lepers are made clean, and the deaf hear, the dead are raised to life, the good news is told to the poor.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And blessed is the person who finds no hindrance in me.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}When John\uc1\u8217*s messengers had left, Jesus, speaking to the crowds, began to say with reference to John,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}\uc1\u8220*What did you go out into the wilderness to look at? A reed waving in the wind? If not, what did you go out to see? A man dressed in rich clothing? Why, those who are accustomed to fine clothes and luxury live in royal palaces.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}What then did you go to see? A prophet? Yes, I tell you, and far more than a prophet.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}This is the man of whom scripture says \uc1\u8211*
