{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 51}As the days before his being taken up to heaven were growing few, Jesus set his face resolutely in the direction of Jerusalem; and he sent on messengers in advance.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 52}On their way, they went into a Samaritan village to make preparations for him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 53}but the people there did not welcome him, because his face was set in the direction of Jerusalem.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 54}When James and John saw this, they said, \uc1\u8220*Master, do you wish us to call for fire to come down from the heavens and consume them?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 55}But Jesus turned and rebuked them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 56}And they made their way to another village.
