{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 10}After this, the Master appointed seventy-two other disciples, and sent them on as his messengers, two and two, in advance, to every town and place that he was himself intending to visit.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8220*The harvest,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*is abundant, but the laborers are few. Therefore pray to the owner of the harvest to send laborers to gather in his harvest.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Now, go. Remember, I am sending you out as my messengers like lambs among wolves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Do not take a purse with you, or a bag, or sandals; and do not stop to greet anyone on your journey.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Whatever house you go to stay at, begin by praying for a blessing on it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Then, if anyone there is deserving of a blessing, your blessing will rest on him; but if not, it will come back on yourselves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Remain at that same house, and eat and drink whatever they offer you; for the worker is worth their wages. Do not keep changing from one house to another.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Whatever town you visit, if the people welcome you, eat what is set before you;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}cure the sick there, and tell people that the kingdom of God is close at hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}But, whatever town you go to visit, if the people do not welcome you, go out into its streets and say{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8216*We wipe off the dust of your town which has clung to Our feet; still, be assured that the kingdom of God is close at Hand.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}I tell you that the doom of Sodom will be more bearable on that day than the doom of that town.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Alas for you, Chorazin! Alas for you, Bethsaida! For, if the miracles which have been done in you had been done in Tyre and Sidon, they would have sat in sackcloth and ashes and repented long ago.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Yet the doom of Tyre and Sidon will be more bearable at the judgment than yours.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And you, Capernaum! Will you exalt yourself to heaven? You will be flung down to Hades.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Anyone who listens to you is listening to me, and anyone who rejects you is rejecting me; while the person who rejects me is rejecting him who sent me as his messenger.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}When the seventy-two returned, they exclaimed joyfully, \uc1\u8220*Master, even the demons submit to us when we use your name.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And Jesus replied, \uc1\u8220*I have had visions of Satan, fallen, like lightning from the heavens.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Remember, I have given you the power to trample on snakes and scorpions, and to meet all the strength of the Enemy. Nothing will ever harm you in any way.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Yet do not rejoice in the fact that the spirits submit to you, but rejoice that your names have been enrolled in heaven.\uc1\u8221*
